The first thing I noticed when trying to analyze how tall this man was was the guardrail in the back. In order for a guardrail to be effective, especially when it's on a cliff like that, it must protect people from falling off. That means that it must be somewhere between 4 and 5 feet, as if it was any lower people would run the risk of flopping over. Then, I analyzed from there how many feet it seemingly took to get to the top of his head (2 more), and it seems after those two feet there are only a few inches up from there, hence why I chose 6'3.
